com.siperian.sif.message.am

Class ProcessRulesRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.am.ProcessRulesRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SystemProvider, Serializable

    public class ProcessRulesRequest
extends SiperianRequest
implements SystemProvider
    Processes Activity Manager rules.

    ProcessRules can be used with or without updating data in MRM. To use it with updating data in MRM, you would use an interactionId with the update requests, and use the ProcessRules request to run the Rules on all data that was updated (as recorded in MRM).

    To use ProcessRules without updating data in MRM (that is, transaction data related to a BO - but not stored in MRM - has changed and you want to process the Rules and Actions, both of which may look up transaction data though Remote Packages), use setRelatedRecordKeys(Collection) instead of SiperianRequest.setInteractionId(String).

    Required parameters:

    • RulesInputSiperianObjectUid - Package or Remote Package on which to process rules.
    • OrsId
    • Async - Default is true, return after queuing request or block until finished processing.

    Optional Parameters:

    • ActivityName - Value to be sent with the ActionRequests.
    • InteractionId - Process records previously updated within the same interaction.
    • RelatedRecordKeys - Process only specific records (may be used alone or in addition to InteractionId).

    Usage Examples:

    Process rules for an interactionId of previous put(s) or other updates to base object data:

    ProcessRulesRequest req = new ProcessRulesRequest();
    req.setInteractionId( somePutResponse.getInteractionId() );
    req.setRulesInputSiperianObjectUid(SiperianObjectType.REMOTE_PACKAGE.makeUid("CUSTOMER_RP"));
    ProcessRulesResponse resp = (ProcessRulesResponse)
    sipClient.process(req);
    System.out.println("ProcessRulesResponse: " + resp.getMessage() + " InteractionId=" + resp.getInteractionId());

    Process rules for specific records:

    ProcessRulesRequest req = new ProcessRulesRequest();
    req.setRulesInputSiperianObjectUid(SiperianObjectType.REMOTE_PACKAGE.makeUid("CUSTOMER_RP"));
    req.addRelatedRecordKey(LocalRecordKey.sourceKey("12345", "ACME", SiperianObjectType.PACKAGE.makeUid("ACCOUNT_P")));
    req.addRelatedRecordKey(LocalRecordKey.sourceKey("67890", "ACME", SiperianObjectType.PACKAGE.makeUid("ADDRESS_P")));
    ProcessRulesResponse resp = (ProcessRulesResponse) client.process(req);
    System.out.println("ProcessRulesResponse: " + resp.getMessage() + " InteractionId=" + resp.getInteractionId());
